Name: ProgramLanguage
Description: Designates the programming language used for the command. Supports the use of a controlled vocabulary.

Name: InParameter
Description: Describes the information used by the command as it is identified within the command structure.

Name: OutParameter
Description: Describes the information that results from the command that may be used as input by another object.

Name: Binding
Description: Defines the link between the output of an external object to an InParameter described above.

Name: CommandContent
Description: Content of the command itself expressed in the language designated in Programming Language.
